The paper deals with the task of attributed subgraph mining, which involves finding cohesive subgraphs based on both graph structure and vertex attributes. This task is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including social network analysis (cs.SI), data mining (cs.DM), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). Given that the paper proposes a new approach to solving this task, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in all of these sub-fields. However, the focus on graph and attribute data suggests that cs.SI and cs.DM are the most likely categories.
